    <header>
        <div class="container">
            <h1>Padel: Principles and Strategies</h1>
        </div>
    </header>

    <div class="container main">
        <div class="section">
            <h2>Introduction to Padel</h2>
            <p>Padel is a racket sport that combines elements of tennis and squash. It is played in doubles on an enclosed court about half the size of a tennis court. The game is quick and dynamic, making it a popular choice for players of all ages and skill levels.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="section">
            <h2>Basic Principles</h2>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Serve:</strong> The serve is underhand, and the ball must bounce once in the server's box before being hit.</li>
                <li><strong>Scoring:</strong> The scoring system is the same as in tennis, with points counting as 15, 30, 40, and game.</li>
                <li><strong>Walls:</strong> Players can use the walls surrounding the court to their advantage, allowing for unique angles and shots.</li>
                <li><strong>Equipment:</strong> Padel rackets are solid and perforated, and the balls are similar to tennis balls but with less pressure.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="section">
            <h2>Key Strategies</h2>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Positioning:</strong> Stay close to the net to control the game and put pressure on your opponents.</li>
                <li><strong>Communication:</strong> Constant communication with your partner is essential to coordinate movements and cover the court effectively.</li>
                <li><strong>Defensive Play:</strong> Use lobs to push opponents back and gain time to reposition.</li>
                <li><strong>Offensive Play:</strong> Aim for the corners and use angles to make it difficult for opponents to return the ball.</li>
                <li><strong>Serve and Volley:</strong> Follow your serve to the net to immediately apply pressure on the returner.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="section">
            <h2>Conclusion</h2>
            <p>Padel is a fun and engaging sport that requires strategy, communication, and skill. Whether you're a beginner or an experienced player, understanding the basic principles and key strategies can help you improve your game and enjoy it even more.</p>
        </div>
    </div>

